        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 6 at 4:25AM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 425 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of strong
thunderstorms extending from 10 miles southeast of Ringgold to near
Richwood, or extending from 24 miles west of Jonesboro to 8 miles
southeast of Monroe, moving south at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Monroe, Ruston, Claiborne, West Monroe, Grambling, Jonesboro,
Columbia, Brownsville-Bawcomville, Brownsville-Bawcom, Swartz,
Richwood, Arcadia, Gibsland, Choudrant, Simsboro, Chatham, Hodge,
North Hodge, Dodson and East Hodge.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.

This storm may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional
information and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
